### 4. Elevator States

| State | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| **IDLE** | Not moving, no pending requests |
| **MOVING_UP** | Moving upward, may have stops |
| **MOVING_DOWN** | Moving downward, may have stops |

---

### 5. Scheduling Strategies

| Strategy | Logic |
|----------|-------|
| **Nearest Elevator** | Pick closest elevator |
| **Same Direction First** | Prefer elevator already going toward request |
| **Least Loaded** | Pick elevator with fewest pending stops |

**For Interview:** Implement **Nearest + Same Direction**

```
Priority:
1. Same direction + nearest
2. Idle + nearest
3. Any available
```

---

### 6. LIMITS

| Constraint | Value |
|------------|-------|
| Floors | Configurable (e.g., 10) |
| Elevators | Configurable (e.g., 2-4) |
| Capacity | Out of scope |
| Speed | Same for all elevators |

---

### 7. FAILS & Edge Cases

| Scenario | Handling |
|----------|----------|
| All elevators busy | Queue request until one is available |
| Request for current floor | Open door immediately if idle |
| Same floor requested multiple times | Ignore duplicate |
| Elevator at top/bottom floor | Can only go opposite direction |

