## ⚠️ Common Mistakes

| Mistake | Better Approach |
|---------|-----------------|
| No direction tracking | Elevator must know UP/DOWN/IDLE |
| Random elevator selection | Use dispatch strategy |
| No pending stops management | Use Set to avoid duplicates |
| Complex state machine | Keep simple: 3 states enough |

---

## 💡 Key Insight: Pending Stops

Instead of complex request queues, use a **Set of floors to stop at**:

```python
pending_stops = {5, 8, 12}  # Just floor numbers

# Add stop
pending_stops.add(7)

# Check if should stop
if current_floor in pending_stops:
    open_door()
    pending_stops.remove(current_floor)
```

**Simple and efficient!**

